-find &gt; c:windowssystem32driverStorefileRepository
-find folders beginning with  &gt; &quot;OEM....&quot; 
-run ultraIso , open W7PE.iso
-create folder eg.DRIVERS and copy &quot;OEM....&quot; folders
-save project and burn (or write to usb)

after opening the winPE run &gt; &quot;DriverPackFromFolder&quot;
-select &quot;DRIVERS&quot; folder on CD/DVD or USB ...

for net/wifi config use &quot;PENetwork&quot;
for media download VLC portable ( better before burn &gt; add to ISO )

